				<p class="text-din-medium privacy_section_header">Who We Are</p>

				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet">WHIP is a mission driven start-up organisation whose vision is to create a constructive civic engagement and participation platform.</li>

				<p class="text-din-medium privacy_section_header">What We Do</p>

				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet" style="padding-bottom: 8px;">WHIP makes engaging in the political sphere easy, providing users with tools to directly influence MPs and hold them to account. Users can learn about the legislation in Parliament, influence MPs and rally support for Bills and issues. In addition, users can get their views to MPs, encourage friends on social media to do the same and get updates on how MPs actually vote - all within 1 minute.</li>

				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet">MPs and Organisations can use WHIP to build support for their positions and expand their membership and directly communicate with the electorate.</li>


				<p class="text-din-medium privacy_section_header">Our Mission</p>

				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet" style="padding-bottom: 8px;">WHIP’s mission is to engage, educate and empower, placing Parliament in your hands. We want everyone to be able to enter the political debate and have their voices heard. The void between the electorate and Parliament is ever growing, however, we can close the gap through a rapport between the two.</li> 

				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet">What if every British citizen could see and understand the bills going through Westminster? What if every British citizen could express an opinion on this information? What if every British citizen could see if their MP was listening to their opinions? In other words, have Parliament in your hands.</li> 

