				<p class="text-din-medium privacy_section_header">FAQ’s</p>

				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet text-din-medium">How do we break down Bills?</li>
				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet" style="padding-bottom: 12px;">Our team of researchers review and synthesis Bills currently going through Parliament. The team follows WHIP’s core values of bi-partisanship, transparency and accuracy to provide answers to the following questions:</li>
				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet">The Bills meaning?</li>
				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet">Arguments for?</li>
				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet">Arguments against?</li>
				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet">Who does it impact?</li>
				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet">Potential costs?</li>

				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet text-din-medium" style="padding-top: 16px;">How come not all Bills are on the platform?</li>
				<li class="text-din terms_li_no_bullet">It is early days for WHIP. We will be following as many Bills as possible. However, many Bills being put to Parliament will fail to progress past the first hurdle, for example, a Bill may not receive enough traction within the house. WHIP aims to provide users with information about the Bills likely to be voted on in Parliament and allow them to express their views on policies that have the potential to affect them.</li>

